President Cyril Ramaphosa and KwaZulu-Natal Cooperative Governance MEC – Nomusa Dube-Ncube are visiting Amanzimtoti – one of the areas hardest hit by floods in the Durban metro. This is his first stop on Wednesday morning. He will be visiting all the areas most affected by the floods that ravaged Durban on Monday night. The official death toll now stands at 51, with more than 1000 being displaced. <span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" data-mce-type="bookmark" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span> In eManzimtoti a road has completely caved in, taking with it vehicles and part of a home. The President will visit Chatsworth, Clermont, and Umlazi which are the other areas hardest hit with more than 800 people now left homeless in these areas alone.  Click on audio below: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/680126">Content hosted by iono.fm</a> Click on the video below: 